            <p>6. WEST 9TH. STREET<lb/>
                NEW YORK CITY.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr Morais<lb/>
                546 N 5th St<lb/>
                Philad<hi rend="sup">a</hi><lb/>
                Penna<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>My dear sir and friend<lb/></p>
            <p>When I read of your fortieth<lb/> anniversary I much regretted that I had<lb/> not known it in time to convey my<lb/> earnest wishes for many more years for<lb/> you as a leader in our people.<lb/></p>
            <p>Procrastination&#44; through much<lb/> work and not over good health&#44; has hitherto<lb/> prevented in writing.<lb/></p>
            <p>But now&#44; though I have one<lb/> man dying in west 64th St another dead<lb/> in East 81st St.&#45;&#45;a rehearsal at 6<lb/> and must go to 45th St. to sleep&#44;&#45;&#45;for<lb/> painters in this house half poison me&#45;&#45;<lb/> I snatch the time to wish you happy<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>holydays and many more celebrations of the<lb/> Passover.<lb/></p>
            <p>The universal esteem you enjoy is your<lb/> sweetest recompense for all your trials.<lb/>  May it grow even greater&#44; and may your<lb/> good works bear good and holy fruit for<lb/> generations yet unborn is the sincere<lb/> prayer of<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours most faithfully<lb/>
                H Pereira Mendes.<lb/></p>
            <p>6. West 9.<lb/>
                April 21&#45;&#45;Nissan 13.<lb/> 5651.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
